FOR SALE BY EXPRESSION OF INTEREST

CBRE Agribusiness and Kerr & Co are pleased to present for sale Cheviot Hills, one of the Western District of Victoria's most outstanding properties, situated in an ideal location that is well-suited to large scale agricultural and semi-rural lifestyle pursuits.

Offered for the first time in its illustrious 164 year history, Cheviot Hills comprises an approximate 1,951* hectare landholding, currently operated as a highly productive livestock enterprise, with key features including:

- A large scale, contiguous landholding comprising improved pastures, outstanding soil types and well-developed infrastructure, underpinned by excellent climatic conditions (average annual rainfall of 712* millimetres).

- The stunning, recently renovated Cheviot Hills Homestead, featuring four bedrooms and set within manicured gardens, open lawn areas and garden beds providing ideal entertaining areas and a luxurious country lifestyle. A three bedroom cottage adjoins the main homestead and provides further accommodation.

- Situated in one of Victoria's most fertile and productive agricultural regions and bordering the township of Penshurst; 25* lineal kilometres from Dunkeld / the Grampians; 27* lineal kilometres from Hamilton; 50* lineal kilometres from Port Fairy; 53* lineal kilometres from Warrnambool; 142* lineal kilometres from Ballarat; 182* lineal kilometres from Geelong and 234* kilometres from the Melbourne CBD.

- A highly productive grazing enterprise comprising both cattle and sheep, with an estimated carrying capacity of approximately 30,000* Dry Sheep Equivalents.

- Outstanding farm infrastructure, including a well-designed laneway system, high quality fencing and excellent stock water facilities.

- Additional improvements include a eight-stand woolshed, three dwellings and extensive rural shedding.

- Cheviot Hills represents a rare opportunity to secure one of Western Victoria's most iconic properties, with potential to acquire livestock also an option for prospective purchasers.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE Agribusiness is pleased to present for sale the Rifa Portfolio, a 43,776* hectare diversified and geographically dispersed portfolio of five aggregations including 10,000* Angus breeders.

ASHLEIGH STATION
NEW SOUTH WALES

• Five contiguous holdings comprising a total land area of 4,391* hectares, of which 3,292* hectares (75%) is arable

• Located in the renowned Northern Slopes along the Gwydir Highway (6.5* kilometres frontage)

• Designed as a cattle finishing hub using winter and summer fodder crops combined with improved and native pastures

MIDDLEBROOK
NEW SOUTH WALES

• Two non-contiguous holdings (an amalgamation of four holdings) comprising a total land area of 8,613*
hectares located 36* lineal kilometres south of Tamworth

• Includes 4,000* Angus breeders

• Water Entitlements across the landholding comprise a total of 884* megalitres

COOPLACURRIPA
NEW SOUTH WALES

• A large-scale cattle breeding aggregation comprising three non-contiguous holdings known as Cooplacurripa, Number One and the Nowendoc Saleyards comprising a total land area of 23,976* hectares

• Located on the eastern fall of the Great Dividing Range and benefited by frontage to the Cooplacurripa River, Rowleys River and Kerriki Creek 

• Includes 4,300* breeders

• Water Entitlements across the aggregation comprise a total of 682* megalitres

BLACKWOOD
VICTORIA

• A large-scale livestock (breeding and finishing) and cropping enterprise comprising a total land area of 2,406* hectares, with 2,100* hectares (87%) arable

• Located in the Western District, one of Australia’s most fertile and productive agricultural regions

• Predominately a pasture based enterprise with minimal supplementary feeding

• Includes 1,800* Angus breeders.

KULWIN PARK
VICTORIA

• A mixed dryland cropping and grazing enterprise, comprising a total land area of 4,390* hectares, with 3,996* hectares (91%) arable

• Located in the Southern Mallee, approximately 65* lineal kilometres
south of Swan Hill

• Highly productive and strong performing dryland cropping enterprise, historically planted to
barley, grazing oats and hay
